cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with joint representations of images and text, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image captioning and text-to-image synthesis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel semi-supervised framework that models shared information between domains and domain-specific information separately, which involves machine learning techniques such as normalizing flow-based priors and invertible neural networks. These techniques are commonly used in subfields such as machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, these categories are also likely to be relevant to this paper.
